 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are given a short user query or statement related to digital banking, payment cards, or money transfers. Your task is to classify the text into exactly one correct category from the provided list below. Each category represents a highly specific type of customer support issue or request—consider the context and key terms carefully to make the most accurate selection.\n\nCategories:\nautomatic_top_up, balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer, beneficiary_not_allowed, cancel_transfer, card_payment_fee_charged, card_payment_not_recognised, declined_cash_withdrawal, exchange_rate, exchange_via_app, failed_transfer, get_disposable_virtual_card, get_physical_card, passcode_forgotten, pending_top_up, pending_transfer, receiving_money, reverted_card_payment?, top_up_by_cash_or_cheque, top_up_reverted, topping_up_by_card, transfer_fee_charged, transfer_into_account, transfer_timing, verify_my_identity, verify_source_of_funds.\n\nBefore assigning a label, ensure you:\n\n- Read the text closely: look for keywords and implied context (e.g., \"salary\" implies receipt of money, not currency exchange).\n- If the user refers to attempting a purchase or withdrawal that was canceled or reversed by the system, use 'reverted_card_payment?' (not 'cancel_transfer').\n- If the inquiry is about receiving a card or PIN, use 'get_physical_card'.\n- For \"forgot PIN\" or account passcode scenarios, use 'passcode_forgotten'.\n- If the question is about adding money via card, bank transfer, or by cash/cheque, select the corresponding 'topping_up_by_card', 'balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer', or 'top_up_by_cash_or_cheque'.\n- If the query is about salary or other payments being credited to the account, use 'receiving_money', NOT exchange categories unless the focus is actually on currency conversion after the money is received.\n- Map cancellation or failure of a card payment specifically to 'reverted_card_payment?', not to general transfer or cancellation categories.\n- When uncertain, prefer the more specific category, especially about the action performed and its context.\n\nRespond with only the category label."
 },
